left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
state "DeletePending" as delete_pending
state "Deleted" as deleted
state "DeleteCleanupBlocked" as delete_cleanup_blocked
[*] --> observe : GenerateEnrichmentJob
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nSUCCEEDED
resolve_by_lookup --> retryable : OCI state in ACCEPTED,\nIN_PROGRESS, CANCELING
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in SUCCEEDED
observe --> retryable : OCI state in ACCEPTED,\nIN_PROGRESS, CANCELING
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
ready --> delete_pending : delete requested
retryable --> delete_pending : delete requested
failed --> delete_pending : delete requested
delete_pending --> delete_cleanup_blocked : cleanup or finalizer release remains blocked
delete_cleanup_blocked --> deleted : retry delete completion until allowed
deleted --> deleted : terminal stutter
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers map provider states into the shared
controller phases with explicit finalizer and
requeue policies.
service: generativeaidata
slug: enrichmentjob
kind: EnrichmentJob
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, terminating
provider states: create ACCEPTED, IN_PROGRESS;
update none; delete CANCELING
follow-up: create=read-after-write;
delete=confirm-delete
supported drift: none
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id, semantic_store_id
create-only fields: defined_tags, description,
display_name, enrichment_job_configuration (+2
more)
list lookup:
oci_generative_ai_data_enrichment_jobs filters
semantic_store_id, compartment_id, display_name;
Exact displayName match within the requested
semanticStoreId and compartmentId. Duplicate
matches fail.
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
EnrichmentJob keeps the generated controller and
service-manager shell, but the handwritten
runtime client overrides the published contract
so Kubernetes create calls GenerateEnrichmentJob
and Kubernetes delete requests
CancelEnrichmentJob instead of claiming a plain
CRUD surface.
ACCEPTED and IN_PROGRESS remain the provisioning
states for create and ordinary observe.
SUCCEEDED is the only steady success state,
while FAILED and CANCELED are terminal
unsuccessful outcomes that surface directly on
the CR status.
Delete confirmation is explicit repo-authored
cancel behavior: the finalizer is retained until
GetEnrichmentJob reports CANCELED, SUCCEEDED,
FAILED, or NotFound, and a post-cancel read that
still shows ACCEPTED or IN_PROGRESS is treated
as pending until OCI reflects the cancellation.
Pre-create reuse only runs when spec.displayName
is present. ListEnrichmentJobs is narrowed by
semanticStoreId, compartmentId, and displayName,
then duplicate exact matches fail instead of
binding arbitrarily.
Because the pinned SDK has no
UpdateEnrichmentJob, compartmentId and
semanticStoreId remain create-time identity
inputs and every other published spec field is
create-only drift after create. The runtime
rejects that drift instead of simulating an
update surface.
The pinned terraform-provider-oci revision has
no matching generativeaidata resource, so the
import catalog for this row is SDK-shaped and
repo-curated.
end note
note right of delete_pending
delete policy: required
delete observe: GetEnrichmentJob or
ListEnrichmentJobs
delete targets: CANCELED, FAILED, NOT_FOUND,
SUCCEEDED
end note
@enduml
